    "course_title": "SOCIAL DANCE I",
    "description": "Introduction to basic movement concepts and skills involved in social dancing.\u00a0Covers the fundamental skills in leading and following, rhythm, and style of the Waltz, Fox Trot, Jitterbug/Swing, Tango, and Cha-Cha. Many social dance forms require that participants work in pairs, which will switch throughout the semester. Other dances may be explored.",
